About the job
Maintenance Engineer I / Electrical - Incumbents of this position will serve as a work leader in assisting, instructing and assigning work responsibilities to skilled Electrician I's and II's to;

Test, repair, install and maintain various types of electrical, fire alarm, fire protection, emergency power and life safety systems;
Supervise and train subordinate personnel;
Assign and schedule work assignments for subordinate personnel ensuring quality workmanship and completion schedules are meet on time.
Ensure maintenance logs, work orders, records and drawings are kept neatly organized and up to date.
Foresee problems and take corrective preventative action.
Assist in creating budget requests, provide cost estimates on small to medium renovations and additions for various departments;
Proficient as a customer service provider utilizing techniques and methods to include the latest electronics; maintain adequate inventory and maintenance logs for various systems;
Collaborate with outside contractors through project completions assuring compliance with codes and contractual obligations; and
Determine materials and/or equipment necessary;

Qualified candidates will have experience which demonstrates;
Knowledge of electrical, fire alarm, fire protection sprinkler, various types of special hazard fire protection systems, elevators, escalators, generators, uninterruptible power supply systems, surge protection devices, lightning protection systems, audio/visual systems and master clock systems;
Knowledge of national, state and local electrical, fire protection and life safety system codes.
Ability to administer, enforce and comply with OSHA rules and regulations including daily wear / use of personal protective equipment including arc flash rated uniforms and suits.

In addition to the minimum requirements, the ideal candidate for this position will have experience listed in the preferences below. Candidates with the preferred experience should ensure the information is provided in the application.
EOE

