About the job
Overview

At Page, we promise design that makes lives better. We’re actively seeking talented people to join an empowered employee environment. Page provides architecture, engineering, interiors and consulting services on large, complex projects around the world. We credit the success of our projects that build communities to the global diversity of our people’s backgrounds and experiences. We’re seeking highly creative, committed team members to help us deliver on our promise of making lives better through design. As our market sectors and services grow, we continuously add new opportunities. Will you join us?

Responsibilities
Set up new Revit MEP projects based on existing project templates;
Develop electrical construction documentation under supervision of assigned engineering, design, and BIM supervision;
Develop electrical construction models in AutoCAD MEP and Revit MEP as part of a BIM team;
Create detailed field installation drawings and fabrication drawings;
Create, modify, and update Revit MEP families as required for specific projects;
Perform file management functions such as posting models, downloading model updates, managing links, and historic versioning;
Attend coordination meetings, communicate with other trades, and create/extract reports as required.
Qualifications
A Degree in Electrical Engineering from an accredited school;
Current EIT or ability to sit for EIT exam;
Knowledge of current Revit, AutoCAD and BIM platforms;
Working knowledge of Microsoft Office (Outlook, Word, and Excel) and GoogleMaps;
Demonstrated knowledge of or interest in MEP systems and their installation, with an emphasis on electrical installations preferred;
Possess an understanding of or willingness to learn drawing and modeling organization, detail, and precision.

